race.description: John Oxley Motors Country Boosted Hcp (Bm58)
race.comment: Lightly raced mare ATHENA'S TREASURE (3) returned from a ten-month spell with an emphatic win over 1000m at Scone, winding up from well back on the corner to score running away. Saluted over this distance when second-up last prep and is on track to repeat that feat. ANDREA (9) was friendless in betting first-up at Wyong and was never in the hunt in a 1000m Class 1. Will probably settle back and appreciate the extra furlong today. Can turn things around. WANJINA ROSE (6) carried just one kilo less and finished right on the placegetters' heels in a BM66 over 1250m at Taree recently. Has a strong record here at this distance. Serious contender. AYE AYE SKIPPER (4) dropped back to a 1000m dash at Taree last start which didn't suit. Cherry ripe after three runs back from a spell and looks a major player back out to this preferable journey. It is hard to knock the form of LA CACHE A VIN (8) but he does need to go an extra furlong today. Each-way chance.
